title: Small sandstone stela
comments:
Both registers show the dedicant worshipping divine barks.  On the upper bark, the aegises have ram heads, each topped with a uraeus.  On the lower register, the aegises are falcon-headed topped with sun disks.  The upper bark is labelled "Amun Re Lord of the Thrones of the Two Lands."  The lower one is surmounted by a damaged cartouche, which should be Ramesses II (see E. Van Essche, GM 158, 1997, 84-85, 87).

The desiccant is named Nebdjefau, and he holds the title "chief of the storehouse (Hry Sna) of Amun."
